{
  "texts": [
    "Of the total measured progress of 21, 400× (relative to an LSTM), we find that 846× is achieved through LSTMs to Kaplan Transformers, and nearly 10× is attributable to Chinchilla rebalancing.",
    "Together, these comprise 91% of total relative efficiency gains, the vast majority of our measured progress.",
    "These results are stylized in Figure 6.Though our experiments do not claim to be exhaustive, we compare our findings with estimates from the literature.",
    "Namely, between 2012 to 2023, Ho et al. [2024] found a doubling time of 8 months, or 2.83× per year, for a total efficiency gain of 22, 000×.",
    "In contrast, the growth rate of our CEG multiplier is approximately 2.23× annually, for a total of 6, 930×, of which 2, 700× (89%) is due to scale-dependent changes."
  ]
}